KEY FRAMEWORKS- SSAE SOC2 Type1/Type2

Type1 Provides a description of the controls provided by the audited organization and the auditor opinion based
on the description, BUT does not involve actual testing of controls

- A Type1 report is specifically defined by the SSAE 16 guidance as a "report on a description of a service orginization's system and the suitability of the design controls.

- When performing a Type1 report the auditors will test the design effectiveness of your company's defined controls by examining a sample of 1 item per control.

Type2 covers a minimum period of 6 months and requires testing of the controls and an opinion from the auditor as to the effectivness based on the test
